File: Banks JOHANNESBURG - Banks are racing to get ATM machines in line with COVID-19 regulations. This comes after government took a hard line about them providing hand sanitisers at all cash machines. It has warned that the auto tellers are super-spreaders of the coronavirus. READ: Banks must keep hand sanitisers at ATMs: NDZ Banks that fail to comply face penalties but several are saying that meeting the updated regulations will be a gigantic logistical exercise. They say they may have to close some machines but emphasise they have no problems adhering to the new rules.